cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DC, cs.SE 

This paper discusses the security of DNS resolvers, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on the security of DNS resolvers in the context of network infrastructure (cs.NI) and system software (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the randomization techniques used in DNS resolvers, which relates to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
